args: I won't let you harm these two!
(I can't afford to hesitate.\nI am an Aegis—and their father.)
(My only concern should be their safety.)
Wh-what are you doing?!\nGet behind me, please!
We don't take charity from dragons!
Wh-what's up with them?\nWhy won't they just give up?
We're here to kill you!\nYou won't change our minds!
What has gotten into you two?!
What? It's because you're Saint Starfall?
Saint Starfall—the saint who delivered\npresents on Dragonyule.
A pity play, huh? Spare me.
It isn't pity. They're doing this because\ntoday is Dragonyule.
What the hell does that matter?
Dragonyule is a day to spend with those\nyou care for.
They just want to make sure you can\ndo that.
So even if you were responsible for the\ndeath of their parents, they want to\nhelp you.
I don't wanna hear about my loved ones\nfrom the same kinda monster that stole\n'em from me!
I understand your feelings. I would feel\nthem too, in your position.
But someone has to break this cycle\nof revenge.
If we don't, it will only end up engulfing\nour children.
I'm not suggesting you put your anger\naside forever. If it were that easy, the\nworld would be a much brighter place.
But just for today, can't you accept\ntheir kindness? Surely we can let\nour souls rest for one day.
We can barely stand, boy. If this gets us\nhome in one piece, so be it.
Something about these two...it reminds\nme of my son.
Maybe 'cause he's a kid too.\nOr maybe it's their outfits.
He came to me the other day sayin' he\nwanted to celebrate Dragonyule.

I don't know where he heard about it,
but I told him there's no way we'd
celebrate anything with ＂dragon＂ in
the name.
It became a pretty big argument.
I had a big fight with my dad.
I said some really nasty stuff I didn't even\nmean, and...
He told me he wanted to make amends\nwith you.
That's why he accepted Fydon and Felyx's\npresents.
THAT'S where those came from?!\n*sigh* Kids are so innocent.
Accepting presents from the same\ncreatures that murdered his mother...
Parents and children see completely\ndifferent worlds, it seems...
As a father myself, I can no longer\nfight you. I don't want to make\nyour boy unhappy.
Hah! You were tryin' to kill us just a minute\nago, and you think you can just call\nthis thing off?
I'm always gonna hate dragons.\nNothing can change that.

And I don't get what all this ＂Dragonyule＂
stuff is about, either—but I know how
important it is to spend time with
the people you love.
I can't forget that I'm still a father.
...No. They helped us. I can't just cut\nthem down now.
We'll see. Either way, we're never gonna\nget on with people who protect them.
And yet... Maybe deep down,\nwe want the same thing.\nCome on, let's go.
We both want to see our children smile.
Which means we have to consider what\nwe as parents can do to provide a future\nwhere they can.
Ha HA! Make way for the true Saint\nStarfall has arrived!
What are you two doing here?
Amane and Cleo said you might be\nin danger.
We are glad to find you well.\n...Hold. Are those undelivered\npresents I see?!
Very well. Your king shall lend you his aid!\nLeave the gifts in my benevolent hands,\nand tend to your wounds at the castle.
I appreciate your concern, but we'd prefer\nto keep delivering them ourselves.
My wounds won't slow me down—and I\ndon't want to cut Fydon and Felyx's tenure\nas Saint Starfall short.
I understand. Will you at least let us help?
*sigh* I suppose all good kings must\nendure stubborn vassals. I shall indulge\nyou this once!
With me, young Saint Starfalls!\nAnd you too, reindeer!\nLet us spread merriment to all!
Off we go! Haaaa ha ha ha!
Heh. I'm sure we'll catch up.
Let's get these presents delivered,\nSaint Starfalls!
